{"type":"message","id":"35c3e96b","parentId":"773cfcab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:37:40.489Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_p9zkmx2s1l71_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 033714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The key pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n3. Last pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 033600.md\r\n4. I need to advance the TIC experiment\r\n\r\nThe next action should be to implement the TIC classifier on pulse log files. Let me first check what log files exist and then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending items:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe first concrete step is to implement the TIC classifier. I should:\r\n1. Check what log files exist\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier script\r\n3. Run it on the pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me start by listing the log files and then creating the TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires a classifier to analyze pulse logs for invariant vs variant content. The logs directory exists but I need to verify its contents and then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants and variants, then measure classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction performance.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Overview\r\nTIC tests the hypothesis: **causal structure IS invariant structure**.\r\nA compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Algorithm\r\n1. Extract content tokens from pulse logs\r\n2. Compute occurrence frequency across time window (last N pulses)\r\n3. Classify as INVARIANT if frequency > λ threshold, else VARIANT\r\n4. Predict next pulse from invariant set\r\n5. Measure accuracy metrics\r\n\r\n## Parameters\r\n- λ (lambda): significance threshold (default: 0.7)\r\n- window: number of pulses to analyze (default: 20)\r\n- min_occurrences: minimum occurrences for invariant classification\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Classification: >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- Prediction: >60% next-pulse content match\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n```powershell\r\npwsh tic_classifier.ps1 -WindowSize 20 -Lambda 0.7\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Output\r\n- Classification results per token\r\n- Invariant set (stable across pulses)\r\n- Variant set (changing across pulses)\r\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24 for TIC experiment*\r\n\"\r\nfile: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n`\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:37:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774337860488}}
